supportDesc.condition: Very worn. A vertical crack on has been repaired at an unnown occasion with two brass plaques, fastened with five screws on each. Leather torn on , exposing some of the raised bands.

p.note: Top left corner: National Library book label with the current signum in black ink. In black ink by a modern hand: Kongl. Bibliotheket 175 blad 1858.
Paper label with the former signum 7 in brown ink.
Fragment of antiphonary, possibly 12th century, with neumatic notation.

decoDesc.decoNote: Head and tail decorated with a zig-zag pattern in red and green.

binding.p: Late medieval binding. Red leather over wooden boards. 6 double raised bands and 2 endbands. 2 clasps on , on two hooks with remnants of a strap.

history.provenance:
Hans Johansson, vicar of Husby-Långhundra Church, according to a note on , dated 20 December 1422, see SDHK
. Antiquities Archive, listed in U 90:4, p. 49, no. 7, U 93, A 6 (current signum).
history.acquisition: From the Antiquities Archive to the National Library.

bibl.title: Lindberg (1923)
bibl.note: Lindberg erroneously locates the missal to Skara diocese

msItem.title: Proper of time
msItem.explicit: In resurrectione tua Christe alleluya. Celum et terra letentur.
msItem.note: The beginning is mutilated; on the first lines of the office for St Sylvester. Ca 20 leaves are missing after . The text ends with the Easter antiphon Sedit angelus.

msItem.title: Ordo and Canon missae
msItem.rubric: Dicto offertorio et calice preparato sacerdos stans in medio altaris et dicat.
msItem.explicit: sit te miserante propiciabile in vitam eternam. Amen.

msItem.title: Proper of time (continued)
msItem.explicit: in nostra mente uitiosum est tue ipsius meditationis curetur Per dominum

msItem.title: Dedication of the church
msItem.rubric: In dedicatione ecclesie ad missam officium.
msItem.incipit: Terribilis est locus iste hic domus dei est
msItem.explicit: Qui viuis et regnas cum domino patre in vnitate spiritus sancti deus.

msItem.explicit: Ego sum uitis vera. participacione numeris

supportDesc.condition: Several leaves missing at the beginning and end of the codex. Ca 20 leaves missing after . Reparation on .
